Sentencas: Mixed ionic electronic conductors (MIECs) have attracted increasing attention as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) and they hold great promise for lowering the operation temperature of SOFCs.
Titulo: Model-guided design of a high performance and durability Ni nanofiber/ ceria matrix solid oxide fuel cell electrode

Sentencas: However, there has been a lack of understanding of the performance-limiting factors and guidelines for rational design of composite metal-MIEC electrodes.
Titulo: Model-guided design of a high performance and durability Ni nanofiber/ ceria matrix solid oxide fuel cell electrode

Sentencas: Using a newly-developed approach based on 3D-tomography and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy, here for the first time we quantify the contribution of the dual-phase boundary (DPB) relative to the three-phase boundary (TPB) reaction pathway on real MIEC electrodes.
Titulo: Model-guided design of a high performance and durability Ni nanofiber/ ceria matrix solid oxide fuel cell electrode

Sentencas: A new design strategy is developed for Ni/gadolinium doped ceria (CGO) electrodes (a typical MIEC electrode) based on the quantitative analyses and a novel Ni/CGO fiber-matrix structure is proposed and fabricated by combining electrospinning and tape-casting methods using commercial powders.
Titulo: Model-guided design of a high performance and durability Ni nanofiber/ ceria matrix solid oxide fuel cell electrode

Sentencas: With only 11.5 vol% nickel, the designer Ni/CGO fiber-matrix electrode shows 32% and 67% lower polarization resistance than a nano-Ni impregnated CGO scaffold electrode and conventional cermet electrode respectively.
Titulo: Model-guided design of a high performance and durability Ni nanofiber/ ceria matrix solid oxide fuel cell electrode

Sentencas: The results in this paper demonstrate quantitatively using real electrode structures that enhancing DPB and hydrogen kinetics are more efficient strategies to enhance electrode performance than simply increasing TPB.
Titulo: Model-guided design of a high performance and durability Ni nanofiber/ ceria matrix solid oxide fuel cell electrode
